thread.title: St. Elizabeth wins softball district title
thread.title_full: St. Elizabeth wins softball district title

author: News Tribune
title: St. Elizabeth wins softball district title
text:
ST. ELIZABETH, Mo. — St. Elizabeth defeated Crocker 2-1 on Friday to win the Class 1 District 3 championship. 
In the sixth inning, Sara Struemph drove in Courtney Scheulen — who tripled — for the winning run. 
Regan Wilde was the winning pitcher in the circle, allowing five hits and striking out five batters. 
Struemph finished with two hits and the game-winning RBI and Brooke Struemph had a hit for a RBI. 
St. Elizabeth (8-14) moves on to host Van-Far in sections on Wednesday. ﻿
